German translation for Freeciv
==============================

Upstream homepage: http://freeciv.org

This is the German translation for Freeciv.

How to get a translation file
-----------------------------

First you need to clone Freeciv’s Subversion repository and configure freeciv:

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$ svn co svn://svn.gna.org/svn/freeciv/branches/S2_4 freeciv-2.4
$ cd freeciv-2.4
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure --prefix=/opt/freeciv-trans
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Now change into the `po/` directory and have the translation file created for you:

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$ cd po
$ make de.pox
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

The resulting `de.pox` file is the file you want to work on. When
you’ve finished doing your translations, copy it into this repository
and commit the changes.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$ cp de.pox $THISREPO
$ cd $THISREPO
$ git add .
$ git commit
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Testing it
----------

After you did a number of commits, you should test your translations. Overwrite
the original `po/de.po` in the Freeciv repository file with your `de.pox` file
(and remove the now unnecessary `de.pox` file in there).

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$ cd $FREECIVREPO/po
$ cp $THISREPO/de.pox de.po
$ rm de.pox
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Then compile Freeciv and install it. Note you do *not* have to reconfigure
Freeciv as you already did this at the very beginning.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
$ cd ..
$ make
$ make install
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Run `/opt/freeciv-trans/bin/freeciv-gtk2` and enjoy your new translations.
If you don’t find them good, fix them. If you do find them good, submit the
new `de.po` file in compressed format (XZ preferred) to `freeciv-i18n@gna.org`.
